        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 3:25PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bagwell, or 13 miles west of Clarksville, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Clarksville, Idabel, Goodlake, Woodland, Redland, Haworth,
Kanawha, Glover, Garvin, Kiomatia, Oak Hill, Golden, Farmers Hill,
Millerton, Negley, Harris, Silver City, English, and Bagwell.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
